This project simulates a brute force attack on an SSH service and demonstrates detection and analysis using Splunk SIEM.
tools used
Kali Linux
Ubuntu
Splunk
Hydra
Attack Simulation
Conducted SSH brute force attack using Hydra
Target system generated multiple failed login attempts
Detection & Analysis
Logs ingested into Splunk
Searched for:
"Failed password"
Identified attacker IP and attack pattern
findings
High volume of failed login attempts from single IP
Pattern consistent with brute force attack
Potential risk of unauthorized access
mitigation
Implement account lockout policy
Use fail2ban
Disable root login
Use SSH key authentication
